Rail chaos sparked by toy grenadeA GREANADE alert in Coatbridge that led to houses being evacuated and rail disruption has been blamed on a toy.Workman discovered what they believed to be a working grenade on Burnbank Street at 1.10pm and bomb disposal experts were called to the scene.Rail travel was affected and a number of homes were evacuated as a precaution while the suspected device was dealt with.Police have confirmed the item found was a toy grenade and people have been allowed back to their homes.Rail travel in the area has also returned to normal.